timeline.bodyText:
Instead of
if (b) {
x = y
} else {
x = z
}
you can write
x = if(b) {
y
} else {
z
}
Or if there are more cases use 'when'
https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/control-flow.html

Please change it to this:
return when {
    initialDirection !in bounceRange -> initialDirection
    initialDirection >= 0  -> axis - initialDirection
    else -> -axis - initialDirection
}.toFloat()

Please use apply.:
sprite.look.apply {
            width = WIDTH
            height = HEIGHT
            ...
}

The project variable could be local.
But you can completely avoid it, again with scope functions:
val context = MockUtil.mockContextForProject()
ProjectManager.getInstance().currentProject = Project(context, "Test", false).apply {
            xmlHeader.virtualScreenWidth = SCREEN_WIDTH
            xmlHeader.virtualScreenHeight = SCREEN_HEIGHT
}

OR
Project(MockUtil.mockContextForProject(), "Test", false).apply {
            xmlHeader.virtualScreenWidth = SCREEN_WIDTH
            xmlHeader.virtualScreenHeight = SCREEN_HEIGHT
            ProjectManager.getInstance().currentProject = this
}
